storyInfo: The Grand Knight Territory is like a lighthouse, flooding the eyes of all of Kazimierz with its dazzling light. But even as tides of people surge into the Territory, one can occasionally see some figures moving against the flow.

attributes.content: Monique.
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Team 3, follow my lead.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Centaurea doesn't get to decide where she goes.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Stop her at all costs. Dead or alive.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Roger!
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: And whatever you do... do not let uninvolved parties know what's going on.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Execute the plan.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: This is the choice you made.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Centaurea.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: (Exhales) ...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: If Roy was here, I wouldn't stand the slightest chance...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: But short one Lazurite, if we're just talking about escape... then I might have a pretty good shot...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Heh...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Who would ever expect that the Platinum of the Armorless Union would one day be hiding in Area 0 that is controlled by the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Looks like break time's over.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Would she really be hiding over here?
attributes.name: Team 3 Member A

attributes.content: We've searched everywhere else.
attributes.name: Team 3 Member B

attributes.content: True...
attributes.name: Team 3 Member A

attributes.content: Lighter on your toes though. Don't alert the patrolling campaign knights. The situation in this place is way too precarious right now.
attributes.name: Team 3 Member B

attributes.content: I know, I know.
attributes.name: Team 3 Member A

attributes.content: (I'm still pretty far from the nearest port...)
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: (After crossing the industrial sector from Area 0, I'll have to decide if I want to take the residential sector or commercial sector to the docks.)
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: (It's way too far...)
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: (But if I can at least make it out of the industrial sector, I'll have sort of a fighting chance.)
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Who's over there?
attributes.name: Team 3 Member A

attributes.content: Stop sneaking around and reveal yourself!
attributes.name: Team 3 Member A

attributes.content: (Lifts shortbow)
attributes.name: Team 3 Member A

attributes.content: You an Infected? Or something else?
attributes.name: Team 3 Member A

attributes.content: (Just a little closer...)
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: (Whispers) Found something?
attributes.name: Team 3 Member B

attributes.content: (Whispers) There's something there, right around the corner.
attributes.name: Team 3 Member A

attributes.content: (Whispers) I'll cover you.
attributes.name: Team 3 Member B

attributes.content: (Whispers) Okay.
attributes.name: Team 3 Member A

attributes.content: Look at that...
attributes.name: Team 3 Member B

attributes.content: It's Platinum's quiver. She must be around here.
attributes.name: Team 3 Member A

attributes.content: Don't move!
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Nn... Nngh!
attributes.name: Team 3 Member A

attributes.content: Tell me, where's Monique headed? What's she planning?
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Tell me, and I might let you live.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: I... I don't know...
attributes.name: Team 3 Member A

attributes.content: Hmph... We're both Armorless here. You know exactly what those words mean.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Maybe you could use some help jogging your memory.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Reporting in!
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Talk to me.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: One of our teams was detained by the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi while searching Area 0.
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Detained?
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: They seem to have run into campaign knights during their mission. They were all injured.
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Should we...
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: They think we're just in Area 0 to take out the K.G.C.C.'s dirty laundry... Let them think that.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: But things aren't so simple.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: And where is the gathering in Area 0?
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: The residential sector.
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Good.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Notify the hunters in the residential sector to start moving in on the commercial sector.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Reporting in!
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Talk to me.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Platinum has appeared at the specified location!
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Heh.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Get ready to round her up.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Roger!
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: (Team 3 should be enough to catch her. But... how much does she know about the way we hunt?)
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: (If she tries to flee to the main street...)
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: It's me. If you have so much free time on your hands, why not come help out?
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Ahaha... We all have our own jobs to do, no? I'm a busy man, you know.
attributes.name: Roy

attributes.content: So, what's the situation?
attributes.name: Roy

attributes.content: My team will flush her out, and I will personally finish the job. Clean and quick.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Today's a good day to hunt.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Glad to hear it. But just in case, let me remind you once more.
attributes.name: Roy

attributes.content: The K.G.C.C. has realized that they've lost control of Darksteel, but we aren't ready yet. Don't let them catch wind of which side we're on.
attributes.name: Roy

attributes.content: ......I know.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Centaurea still holds the Platinum seat on the Board of Directors. Make sure to come up with a good excuse.
attributes.name: Roy

attributes.content: ...Roy.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Haha, don't worry. Just in case... those three magnanimous bosses of ours will do us a favor.
attributes.name: Roy

attributes.content: Huff... Huff...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Almost there.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Once I get through the commercial sector, I can get out of Kazimierz.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Ugh...!
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Drop your weapon, Platinum.
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Monique promises that as long as you do what we say and head back, the Union is willing to overlook your betrayal.
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Heh... We're all Armorless here. Spare me the horseshit.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Don't even try to resist. We've blocked off all the exits and you have nowhere to run. If you know what's good for you, you'll––
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Nngh––!
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: *pant*... *pant*... Leave the negotiations to the professionals. You bunch... should work on your aim first.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: (As long as I can blend in with the crowd in the commercial sector...)
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: (...then I'll still have a chance.)
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: (Just a little more...)
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Some are already moving to guard the exits.
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: In any case, she's still Platinum, and won't go down without a fight.
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: After her. Don't disappoint Monique.
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Where do you think you're going?
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Surrender already, Platinum.
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Let's... try this again.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: I don't want to end up like the old man, dying in a place like this... Heh. At least let me die somewhere I can see the sky......
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Do it.
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Haaah!
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Graah!
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: *cough*, *cough* *cough*...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Down to my last arrow, huh...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Gah.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: What young knights need is experience, not the decadence brought by competition knights weaned on the teats of prosperity!
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Rhodes Island is a trustworthy company. They've won Gravel's loyalty, and there's no reason not to let her go out and see the world.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: ––That is what the Grand Knight said to my master.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Woah, Gravel, your impression is pretty dead-on, even if you don't change your voice at all.
attributes.name: Hibiscus

attributes.options: I agree. It's amazing.;......;How come you never told me you could do that?

attributes.content: The key is to hit all the important points. I wouldn't even call it a skill. It's just that I had to relay messages to my master a lot.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: This 'master', do you mean the Knight Primus of the family that raised you?
attributes.name: Hibiscus

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Did he agree to let you go?
attributes.name: Hibiscus

attributes.content: I... haven't tried to convince him yet. But I will do it.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: The last time I brought it up, he got so mad he chased me out of the house...
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: I see...
attributes.name: Hibiscus

attributes.content: *cough* *cough*... Haah... Ugh...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Almost there... Just a bit more...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Platinum & Hibiscus

attributes.content: In a flash, Gravel's blade finds its way to Platinum's neck.
The only reason she stays her hand is the total exhaustion of the powerful enemy before her. Killing her couldn't be any easier.
Are you okay?
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Ow, owwww... I'm fine, but... Agh! You're seriously hurt!
attributes.name: Hibiscus

attributes.content: Trouble seems to have found you, Platinum.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: None of your business... hng.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Sh-She can't walk straight, but I'm not seeing any open wounds... Is she just exhausted, or...
attributes.name: Hibiscus

attributes.content: It's the Armorless Union. They've caught up.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Rebel? Or are you the traitor?
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: D-Doctor!
attributes.name: Hibiscus

attributes.content: The Armorless collapsed on the ground before you is nothing like the elegant assassin of your impressions.
You're... the Doctor... from Rhodes Island...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Are the outsiders... all like you?
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: I'm here.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.options: I don't expect the Armorless Union to let us off easily.;We may be in danger as soon as we leave the protection of the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi.;The K.G.C.C. is just a single shield, one that won't hold for long.

attributes.content: To be honest, I was hoping to bring this up with you.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: After all, the enemy operates from the shadows. In Kazimierz, the Armorless Union has countless ways to torment your company.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.options: Hibiscus, tend to her wounds first!;Gravel, hold back the Armorless Union!

attributes.content: Hehe, as you wish.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Hold on, okay? You listening, Miss Armorless?
attributes.name: Hibiscus

attributes.content: Why?
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.options: I'll explain on the way back. We can talk about your payment later.;......;I just have a big heart. Helping others is like helping myself.

attributes.content: After her! We mustn't let her get away! Contact Monique!
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Damn it! Why are you getting on our way?!
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Who knows?
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Maybe this is why the Radiant Knight was willing to trust Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: We don't have time to waste on you.
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: That's right.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: We're short on time. To make matters worse, our activities have been exposed to a campaign knight.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Judging by your tone, you plan on killing me?
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Sigh...
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: For some time now, it seems that whenever I try to get some work done, uninvited guests always end up getting in my way.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Heh. So sorry about that, Lazurite.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: I have a request from the Doctor. By its nature, that takes priority over work.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: I can't take you in a fight head-on, but stopping you from landing a clean shot should be no problem for me.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Rhodes Island, huh.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Without the Radiant Knight and those strange Sarkaz behind you, don't you think you're overestimating yourself a bit?
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Even from this distance, I can easily put an arrow through both that Doctor of yours and Platinum. Hardly a tall ask.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Your presumptuousness is about to cost you a lot more lives, knight.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Let's see if you can stop me.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: ––Hah!
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Wait, hold on!
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Monique!
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: I know! And who gave you permission to order me around?!
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: ...Platinum. We have no more need for a Platinum.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Go to hell, along with that meddlesome Sarkaz doctor.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Dammit!
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Her pride forbids her from missing again.
Monique draws back her longbow.

attributes.text: Who dares to harm Rhodes Island's medical staff?

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: The arrow's steel head corrodes and deteriorates. The shaft gradually softens into a branch with young shoots, falling gently into her hand.
The figure in the distance is but a wavering speck, and Monique feels a discomfort spreading throughout her entire body.
It is a sense of imminent danger.
The small Caprinae takes gentle steps forward, bearing a calm and leisurely casting pose that seems ill-suited to the battlefield.
I was just thinking how rarely my line of work brings me back to the landship, and how nice it would be to touch base again. Imagine my surprise when I happened across this lovely scene.
attributes.name: Touch

attributes.content: Who are you?
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: You aren't privy to that information, Armorless.
attributes.name: Touch

attributes.content: It's normally against my principles to interfere with matters outside of work, but just now, you seem to have shown clear hostilities against a fleeing member of Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Touch

attributes.content: That isn't allowed, Armorless.
attributes.name: Touch

attributes.content: Nngh...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Easy now. Your wounds are deep.
attributes.name: Hibiscus

attributes.content: Ugh... I...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Don't worry. Once we get through the commercial sector, we'll be able to see Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Hibiscus

attributes.content: Platinum has not slept since she started running three days ago.
She dared not eat or drink, out of fear that anything she bought might be a trap set by the Armorless Union.
Rhodes Island...
She turns and casts her gaze backwards. It's the Doctor of Rhodes Island.
The leader of a foreign organization that always ruins her plans.
Her savior.
Ironic.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: She contemplates whether or not she wants to keep up appearances in front of the Doctor. She ponders whether or not she wants to ask to be taken away from the Grand Knight Territory. She...
...still has not awoken from beneath that ensorcelled sky.
Hm...
attributes.name: Touch

attributes.content: It would appear that optimism alone is not enough for just two to stop a Lazurite.
attributes.name: Touch

attributes.content: Really? I think we've already done a pretty good job, given how many we're up against.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Grr. That campaign knight is still able to put up a fight after taking such a beating because of your Arts, huh?
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: How do you know who I am? Are you from Kazimierz?
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: You ask too many questions, Armorless. Let's try to work things out slowly.
attributes.name: Touch

attributes.content: If that's what you want. You seem to be more of a medic than that Sarkaz–– But in other words, you can't hold me off for as long.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Since you seem to know so much about the Armorless Union, then you should know that we have something much more terrifying–
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Please, go on.
attributes.name: Touch

attributes.content: This knight and I, we're not the kind to kick others when they're down.
attributes.name: Touch

attributes.content: ...Right.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Gah... Fine.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Have it your way.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Monique?
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: We're pulling out.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: The campaign knights have noticed the commotion. Don't draw any unnecessary attention.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Huh? But, our scouts didn't find any knights nearby–
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Don't make me repeat myself.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Yes, of course! All forces, regroup!
attributes.name: A Team 3 Member

attributes.content: Consider yourself lucky.
attributes.name: Monique

attributes.content: Lucky?
attributes.name: Touch

attributes.content: We make our own luck, Armorless.
attributes.name: Touch

attributes.content: I'm curious, Młynar.
How many years has it been?
How many years have you spent, tilling the land of Kazimierz like a burdenbeast? Kirill passed without seeing you change a single thing.
How many enemies and opponents have you tormented, giving them no respite even in their nightmares?
Even with you doing nothing at all, it took them so long to believe... that Młynar Nearl would no longer be a thorn in their side.
You were still young back then. You were in your prime. But for Kirill's sake, for the sake of the two kids that would come after you, you chose to remain in Kazimierz.
After all these years, even I thought you had long given up.
But why now? Why did you decide to leave the Grand Knight Territory?
You don't need to know.
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: You know that the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi's deepest secrets are still hidden under those gaudy lights, right? Beneath the Grand Knight Territory's Wall of Champions.
What did the archivist tell you? No, someone that stubborn would never let anything slip... That means, this was the Grand Knight's intention?
I'm just enjoying my well-deserved vacation.
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: Then I look forward to you returning to your post after your vacation, Młynar.
You don't need to worry about that.
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: ...I've lived a very long time, Młynar.
While I still remember, you ignited the Leithanien conspiracy. Incandescent waves would swallow entire enemy formations...
You culled those traitorous knights, one by one, like a farmer harvesting wheat.
The Radiant Knight's glow is but an empty pallor. What pleases me more is your boundless light, your wrath.
And since then, I've believed that if I ever saw your radiance once more, I would need...
...to take your life.
And you?
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: Hm?
After over half a century, this is the final destination you would choose for the Armorless Union you crafted with your own hands?
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: I simply made the wisest decision. You should understand my rationale.
Oho... Or, has the Radiant Knight made you believe that the Nearl family can forge a new future? Have you accepted her idealistic, impossible path?
You speak of paths, and the future.
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: The Nearl knights have never needed others to judge the directions of their paths. I just didn't believe those girls had the power to stay on that path.
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: Nor did I believe... in the companions they found.
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: But that was then.
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: Heh...
You have a point. You and the Radiant Knight are of a kind.
The only difference is you're more disillusioned than she is. You believe in the country less than she does. That's all.
It is a pity. I had thought that our disillusionment and wrath were one and the same.
You did everything you could to try to integrate into the General Chamber of Commerce. Don't you dare lump me in with you.
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: The time for reminiscing is over.
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: What, it's not enough that the Armorless Union will no longer harm Rhodes Island or the Nearl family? Is that not enough to show my sincerity?
It is enough.
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: Otherwise your corpse would already be outside, collecting the sun and rain.
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: You know better than me all the things the Union has done.
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: We've never seen eye to eye... 'Darksteel.'
attributes.name: Młynar

attributes.content: Ahh, as harsh as ever.
Goodbye, Młynar. I hope that your vacation... will prove fruitful.

attributes.options: Are you feeling any better?;......;It stopped hurting, right?

attributes.content: Just because the Lazurites went after me does not mean that I've lost my standing in the Union... I might still be answering to the Board of Directors.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: You have to know that, but...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.options: I think this will be a win-win situation.;......;We'll figure it out.

attributes.content: Darn you! After all the trouble we all went through, can't you at least show some gratitude like a normal person?
attributes.name: Hibiscus

attributes.content: Th-Thank you, Doctor.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Phew...
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: You sure know how to put a girl in a rough spot, Doctor.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Relax, Zalak. The treatment works better that way.
attributes.name: Touch

attributes.content: Thanks...
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Gravel! How'd you end up with Instructor Touch?
attributes.name: Hibiscus

attributes.content: Sheer coincidence.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Sorry, but would you mind letting me sit and chat for a bit?
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Ah, of course! Instructor, if you'd like...
attributes.name: Hibiscus

attributes.content: No need. I'm just here to report back to Amiya.
attributes.name: Touch

attributes.content: Taking on a Lazurite was no easy task.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: But, this counts as a win, right?
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: You owe me big time, haha.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.options: Let's head back to Rhodes Island.

attributes.content: Seems like you and Platinum have reached an agreement.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Enemies one moment, chatting and shaking hands the next moment.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: That's special.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Nnnnh... Maybe I should take a break too...
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: What are you plotting now, Armorless?
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: You're staring at me.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Until you leave Kazimierz... No, until you get away from the Doctor, I'll always have my eye on you.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Heh... After all, you said it yourself. If the Armorless Union was ever to rebel, the K.G.C.C. might come to you in private...
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Don't think you're absolved of your sins just because the Doctor saved you, murderer. Your bloodstained hands will never know trust, Armorless.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Can't argue with that.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: But don't worry. At least for now, I have to work hard to earn the Doctor's trust. If you don't even know the basics, you'll never make it in the Grand Knight Territory.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Are you making fun of me?
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: That's too much effort. Don't sweat it.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Are you leaving Kazimierz with Rhodes Island?
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: What's it to you?
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Rough times are ahead of us...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: This is the first time... I've ever been on a landship like this.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Hah... That Doctor... really is strange.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Strange? That's no way to talk about the one who saved your life.
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Fair enough.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Will we come back here?
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: Do you want to?
attributes.name: Gravel

attributes.content: Hm...
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: No clue. Never gave it much thought.
attributes.name: Platinum

attributes.content: But for now, I just want to leave.
attributes.name: Platinum
